alcatelIND1BGPMIBObjects.description: Branch For Border Gateway Protocol (BGP) Subsystem Managed Objects.

alcatelIND1BGPMIBConformance.name: alcatelIND1BGPMIBConformance
alcatelIND1BGPMIBConformance.description: Branch For Border Gateway Protocol (BGP) Subsystem Conformance Information.

alcatelIND1BGPMIBGroups.name: alcatelIND1BGPMIBGroups
alcatelIND1BGPMIBGroups.description: Branch For Border Gateway Protocol (BGP) Subsystem Units Of Conformance.

alcatelIND1BGPMIBCompliances.name: alcatelIND1BGPMIBCompliances
alcatelIND1BGPMIBCompliances.description: Branch For Border Gateway Protocol (BGP) Subsystem Compliance Statements.

alaBgpMedAlways.name: alaBgpMedAlways
alaBgpMedAlways.description: Enable/Disable BGP Metric MULTI_EXIT_DISC comparison between routes from different Autonomous Systems.

alaBgpDefaultLocalPref.name: alaBgpDefaultLocalPref
alaBgpDefaultLocalPref.description: The default LOCAL_PREF to be applied to routes learnt from neighbouring autonomous system.

alaBgpMissingMed.name: alaBgpMissingMed
alaBgpMissingMed.description: Specifies how to a missing med in a path attribute.

alaBgpManualTag.name: alaBgpManualTag
alaBgpManualTag.description: Manual tag to be used. A value of 0 means no manual tagging.

alaBgpPromiscuousNeighbours.name: alaBgpPromiscuousNeighbours
alaBgpPromiscuousNeighbours.description: Enable/Disable BGP to accept connections from neighbours that are not configured.

alaBgpConfedId.name: alaBgpConfedId
alaBgpConfedId.description: Confederation identifier. A value of 0 means this local speaker is not a member of any confederation

alaBgpDampHalfLifeReach.name: alaBgpDampHalfLifeReach
alaBgpDampHalfLifeReach.description: The time in seconds in which the penalty to a flapping route decreases to half its initial value while the route remains reachable. Obsoleted by the variable alaBgpDampHalfLife.

alaBgpDampHalfLifeUnReach.name: alaBgpDampHalfLifeUnReach
alaBgpDampHalfLifeUnReach.description: The time in seconds in which the penalty to a flapping route decreases to half its initial value while the route remains unreachable. Obsoleted by the variable alaBgpDampHalfLife.

alaBgpDampMaxFlapHistory.name: alaBgpDampMaxFlapHistory
alaBgpDampMaxFlapHistory.description: The time in seconds the flap history of a route is retained.

alaBgpDebugLevel.name: alaBgpDebugLevel
alaBgpDebugLevel.description: This object has been deprecated in favour of alaDrcTmBgpDebug Configuration.

alaBgpFastExternalFailOver.name: alaBgpFastExternalFailOver
alaBgpFastExternalFailOver.description: Enable/Disable Resetting session immediately if a link to a directly connected external peer is operationally down.

alaBgpPeerChanges.name: alaBgpPeerChanges
alaBgpPeerChanges.description: Enable/Disable logging of peer state changes to the syslog.

alaBgpNumActiveRoutes.name: alaBgpNumActiveRoutes
alaBgpNumActiveRoutes.description: The number of active known routes in the BGP routing table

alaBgpNumEstabExternalPeers.name: alaBgpNumEstabExternalPeers
alaBgpNumEstabExternalPeers.description: The number of External Peers that are in ESTABLISHED state.

alaBgpNumEstabInternalPeers.name: alaBgpNumEstabInternalPeers
alaBgpNumEstabInternalPeers.description: The number of Internal Peers that are in ESTABLISHED state.

alaBgpNumPaths.name: alaBgpNumPaths
alaBgpNumPaths.description: The total number of paths known to the system.

alaBgpNumFeasiblePaths.name: alaBgpNumFeasiblePaths
alaBgpNumFeasiblePaths.description: The total number of feasible paths known to the system.

alaBgpNumDampenedPaths.name: alaBgpNumDampenedPaths
alaBgpNumDampenedPaths.description: The total number of dampened paths known to the system.

alaBgpNumIgpSyncWaitPaths.name: alaBgpNumIgpSyncWaitPaths
alaBgpNumIgpSyncWaitPaths.description: The total number of paths learnt from internal peers that are waiting to be synchronized with IGP.

alaBgpNumPolicyChgPaths.name: alaBgpNumPolicyChgPaths
alaBgpNumPolicyChgPaths.description: The total number of paths that are currently rejected but stored anticipating an inbound policy change for an external peer which is configured to accept dynamic policy changes.

alaBgpClusterId.name: alaBgpClusterId
alaBgpClusterId.description: The local cluster id of this route reflection cluster.

alaBgpDampeningClear.name: alaBgpDampeningClear
alaBgpDampeningClear.description: Writing a value of clear into this variable will clear the dampening history.

alaBgpDampCutOff.name: alaBgpDampCutOff
alaBgpDampCutOff.description: When a route's figure of merit reaches this value, the route is considered damped. This is a floating point value with 2 digit precision. For example, a value of 3.5 is encoded as 350, a value of 0.9 is encoded as 90 ,a value of 9.45 is encoded as 945.

alaBgpDampReuse.name: alaBgpDampReuse
alaBgpDampReuse.description: When a route's figure of merit decays to this value, the route can be reused. This is a floating point value with 2 digit precision. For example, a value of 3.5 is encoded as 350, a value of 0.9 is encoded as 90 , a value of 9.45 is encoded as 945.

alaBgpDampCeil.name: alaBgpDampCeil
alaBgpDampCeil.description: The maximum value that the figure of merit of a route can attain. This is a floating point value with 2 digit precision. For example, a value of 3.5 is encoded as 350, a value of 0.9 is encoded as 90, a value of 9.45 is encoded as 945.

alaBgpAspathCompare.name: alaBgpAspathCompare
alaBgpAspathCompare.description: Specifies whether to include aspath comparison in route selection.

alaBgpAsOriginInterval.name: alaBgpAsOriginInterval
alaBgpAsOriginInterval.description: The minimum interval in seconds between successive updates advertising the networks belonging to the local autonomous system.

alaBgpDampHalfLife.name: alaBgpDampHalfLife
alaBgpDampHalfLife.description: The time in seconds in which the penalty to a flapping route decreases to half its initial value.

alaBgpRestartInterval.name: alaBgpRestartInterval
alaBgpRestartInterval.description: Determines how long, in seconds, peering BGP routers are told to wait for this router to complete graceful restart and re-establish peering session. It is recommended that this value not be more than the configured Hold Time interval.

alaBgpRestartStatus.name: alaBgpRestartStatus
alaBgpRestartStatus.description: Indicates whether the router is currently performing a graceful restart.

alaBgpMultiProtocolIpv4.name: alaBgpMultiProtocolIpv4
alaBgpMultiProtocolIpv4.description: Indicates whether IPv4 BGP4 capability is enabled.

alaBgpMultiProtocolIpv6.name: alaBgpMultiProtocolIpv6
alaBgpMultiProtocolIpv6.description: Indicates whether IPv6 BGP4 capability is enabled.

alaBgpBfdAllNeighborStatus.name: alaBgpBfdAllNeighborStatus
alaBgpBfdAllNeighborStatus.description: Enables/Disables BFd for all BGP Neighbors.

alaBgpPeerPassive.name: alaBgpPeerPassive
alaBgpPeerPassive.description: Enable/Disable the peer passive status. If enabled the peer will not initiate a transport connection.

alaBgpPeerName.name: alaBgpPeerName
alaBgpPeerName.description: A symbolic name for the neighbour.

alaBgpPeerMultiHop.name: alaBgpPeerMultiHop
alaBgpPeerMultiHop.description: If enabled the external peer is allowed to be multiple hops away.

alaBgpPeerMaxPrefix.name: alaBgpPeerMaxPrefix
alaBgpPeerMaxPrefix.description: The maximum prefixes to be accepted from this peer. If this maximum is reached, the peer will be sent a NOTIFY message with a CEASE ecode.

alaBgpPeerMaxPrefixWarnOnly.name: alaBgpPeerMaxPrefixWarnOnly
alaBgpPeerMaxPrefixWarnOnly.description: If enabled, the operator will be warned when the peer reaches 80% of the configured maximum prefixes. To see this message, BGP debug for type 'warnings' must be activated and debug level set to 20.

alaBgpPeerNextHopSelf.name: alaBgpPeerNextHopSelf
alaBgpPeerNextHopSelf.description: If enabled, nexthop processing in the updates sent to this peer is disabled and is set to the ip address of the interface attached to this peer.

alaBgpPeerSoftReconfig.name: alaBgpPeerSoftReconfig
alaBgpPeerSoftReconfig.description: Enable/Disable dynamic policy configurability on the connection to this peer.

alaBgpPeerInSoftReset.name: alaBgpPeerInSoftReset
alaBgpPeerInSoftReset.description: Route refresh capability is Enabled/Disabled on the connection to this peer.

alaBgpPeerIpv4Unicast.name: alaBgpPeerIpv4Unicast
alaBgpPeerIpv4Unicast.description: Multiprotocol capability IPv4 Unicast is Enabled/Disabled on the connection to this peer .

alaBgpPeerIpv4Multicast.name: alaBgpPeerIpv4Multicast
alaBgpPeerIpv4Multicast.description: Multiprotocol capability IPv4 Multicast is Enabled/Disabled on the connection to this peer .

alaBgpPeerRcvdRtRefreshMsgs.name: alaBgpPeerRcvdRtRefreshMsgs
alaBgpPeerRcvdRtRefreshMsgs.description: The number of route refresh messages received from this peer.

alaBgpPeerSentRtRefreshMsgs.name: alaBgpPeerSentRtRefreshMsgs
alaBgpPeerSentRtRefreshMsgs.description: The number of route refresh messages sent to this peer.

alaBgpPeerRouteMapOut.name: alaBgpPeerRouteMapOut
alaBgpPeerRouteMapOut.description: The name of the policy map to be applied to the updates sent to this peer. This is same as alaBgpPolicyRouteMapName.

alaBgpPeerRouteMapIn.name: alaBgpPeerRouteMapIn
alaBgpPeerRouteMapIn.description: The name of the policy map to be applied to the updates received from this peer. This is same as alaBgpPolicyRouteMapName.

alaBgpPeerLocalAddr.name: alaBgpPeerLocalAddr
alaBgpPeerLocalAddr.description: Local Ip Address of this connection.

alaBgpPeerLastDownReason.name: alaBgpPeerLastDownReason
alaBgpPeerLastDownReason.description: The general reason for termination of last established session with the peer since the protocol was operationally up.

alaBgpPeerLastDownTime.name: alaBgpPeerLastDownTime
alaBgpPeerLastDownTime.description: The time elapsed since the BGP session with the peer was terminated.

alaBgpPeerLastReadTime.name: alaBgpPeerLastReadTime
alaBgpPeerLastReadTime.description: The time elapsed since we last read data from the peer.

alaBgpPeerRcvdNotifyMsgs.name: alaBgpPeerRcvdNotifyMsgs
alaBgpPeerRcvdNotifyMsgs.description: The Number of notification messages received from this peer.

alaBgpPeerSentNotifyMsgs.name: alaBgpPeerSentNotifyMsgs
alaBgpPeerSentNotifyMsgs.description: The Number of notification messages sent to this peer.

alaBgpPeerRcvdPrefixes.name: alaBgpPeerRcvdPrefixes
alaBgpPeerRcvdPrefixes.description: The Number of prefixes received from this peer.

alaBgpPeerDownTransitions.name: alaBgpPeerDownTransitions
alaBgpPeerDownTransitions.description: The Number of times this peer session transitioned to IDLE state.

alaBgpPeerType.name: alaBgpPeerType
alaBgpPeerType.description: This indicates whether the peer belongs to the local autonomous system(internal) or another autonmous system.

alaBgpPeerClearCounter.name: alaBgpPeerClearCounter
alaBgpPeerClearCounter.description: Setting a value of clear into this variable will clear the per peer statistics.

alaBgpPeerAutoReStart.name: alaBgpPeerAutoReStart
alaBgpPeerAutoReStart.description: Enable/Disable the peer autostart status. If enabled, the peer will be automatically restarted (if administratively enabled) after the transition to IDLE state.

alaBgpPeerClientStatus.name: alaBgpPeerClientStatus
alaBgpPeerClientStatus.description: If enabled this peer is a route reflection client.

alaBgpPeerConfedStatus.name: alaBgpPeerConfedStatus
alaBgpPeerConfedStatus.description: If enabled this peer is a member of our confederation.

alaBgpPeerRemovePrivateAs.name: alaBgpPeerRemovePrivateAs
alaBgpPeerRemovePrivateAs.description: If enabled private as numbers are stripped out in the updates sent to this peer.

alaBgpPeerTTL.name: alaBgpPeerTTL
alaBgpPeerTTL.description: TTL count for packets on this TCP connection.

alaBgpPeerAspathListOut.name: alaBgpPeerAspathListOut
alaBgpPeerAspathListOut.description: The name of the aspath-list to be applied to the updates sent to this peer. This is same as alaBgpAspathMatchListId.

alaBgpPeerAspathListIn.name: alaBgpPeerAspathListIn
alaBgpPeerAspathListIn.description: The name of the aspath-list to be applied to the updates received from this peer. This is same as alaBgpAspathMatchListId.

alaBgpPeerPrefixListOut.name: alaBgpPeerPrefixListOut
alaBgpPeerPrefixListOut.description: The name of the prefix-list to be applied to the updates sent to this peer. This is same as alaBgpPrefixMatchListId.

alaBgpPeerPrefixListIn.name: alaBgpPeerPrefixListIn
alaBgpPeerPrefixListIn.description: The name of the prefix-list to be applied to the updates received from this peer. This is same as alaBgpPrefixMatchListId.

alaBgpPeerCommunityListOut.name: alaBgpPeerCommunityListOut
alaBgpPeerCommunityListOut.description: The name of the community-list to be applied to the updates sent to this peer. This is same as alaBgpCommunityMatchListId.

alaBgpPeerCommunityListIn.name: alaBgpPeerCommunityListIn
alaBgpPeerCommunityListIn.description: The name of the community-list to be applied to the updates received from this peer. This is same as alaBgpCommunityMatchListId.

alaBgpPeerRestart.name: alaBgpPeerRestart
alaBgpPeerRestart.description: Setting a value of restart into this variable will restart the peer.

alaBgpPeerDefaultOriginate.name: alaBgpPeerDefaultOriginate
alaBgpPeerDefaultOriginate.description: If enabled a default route is sent to this neighbour.

alaBgpPeerReconfigureInBound.name: alaBgpPeerReconfigureInBound
alaBgpPeerReconfigureInBound.description: Setting a value of reconfigure into this variable will re-start inbound policy evaluation of the peer.

alaBgpPeerReconfigureOutBound.name: alaBgpPeerReconfigureOutBound
alaBgpPeerReconfigureOutBound.description: Setting a value of reconfigure into this variable will re-start outbound policy evaluation of the peer.

alaBgpPeerMD5Key.name: alaBgpPeerMD5Key
alaBgpPeerMD5Key.description: Value of the MD5 key used in TCP connection with the peer. This field is secured and returned value is non significant.

alaBgpPeerMD5KeyEncrypt.name: alaBgpPeerMD5KeyEncrypt
alaBgpPeerMD5KeyEncrypt.description: Value of the MD5 key encrypted using 3DES algorithm. It is calculated from MD5 key value, and is used only to restore configuration on reboot.

alaBgpPeerUpTransitions.name: alaBgpPeerUpTransitions
alaBgpPeerUpTransitions.description: The Number of times this peer session transitioned to ESTABLISHED state.

alaBgpPeerLastWriteTime.name: alaBgpPeerLastWriteTime
alaBgpPeerLastWriteTime.description: The time elapsed since we last sent data to the peer.

alaBgpPeerRcvdMsgs.name: alaBgpPeerRcvdMsgs
alaBgpPeerRcvdMsgs.description: The Number of messages received from the peer.

alaBgpPeerSentMsgs.name: alaBgpPeerSentMsgs
alaBgpPeerSentMsgs.description: The Number of messages sent to the peer.

alaBgpPeerRcvdUpdMsgs.name: alaBgpPeerRcvdUpdMsgs
alaBgpPeerRcvdUpdMsgs.description: The Number of update messages received from the peer.

alaBgpPeerSentUpdMsgs.name: alaBgpPeerSentUpdMsgs
alaBgpPeerSentUpdMsgs.description: The Number of update messages sent to the peer.

alaBgpPeerLastTransitionTime.name: alaBgpPeerLastTransitionTime
alaBgpPeerLastTransitionTime.description: The time elapsed since the BGP session was operationally up or down to the peer.

alaBgpPeerLastUpTime.name: alaBgpPeerLastUpTime
alaBgpPeerLastUpTime.description: The time elapsed since the BGP session with the peer was established.

alaBgpPeerLocalIntfName.name: alaBgpPeerLocalIntfName
alaBgpPeerLocalIntfName.description: The user defined name used to identify the local IP interface for this peer's TCP connection.

alaBgpPeerRestartTime.name: alaBgpPeerRestartTime
alaBgpPeerRestartTime.description: The graceful restart time interval advertised by this peer. A value of 0 indicates that this peer is not capable of graceful restart, and has not advertised this capability.

alaBgpPeerRestartState.name: alaBgpPeerRestartState
alaBgpPeerRestartState.description: Indicates whether the peer is currently performing a graceful restart. A value of none indicates that this peer is not capable of graceful restart.

alaBgpPeerRestartFwdState.name: alaBgpPeerRestartFwdState
alaBgpPeerRestartFwdState.description: Indicates whether the peer has preserved the forwarding state during the graceful restart. This value is defined only for a peer that has advertised graceful restart capability. For peers that are not capable of graceful restart, this value will be notPreserved.

alaBgpPeerIpv6Unicast.name: alaBgpPeerIpv6Unicast
alaBgpPeerIpv6Unicast.description: Indicates whether the peer has advertised Multiprotocol IPv6 Unicast capability in its BGP OPEN message.

alaBgpPeerIpv6NextHop.name: alaBgpPeerIpv6NextHop
alaBgpPeerIpv6NextHop.description: The IPv6 nexthop for IPv6 routes advertised to this peer.

alaBgpPeerLocalPort.name: alaBgpPeerLocalPort
alaBgpPeerLocalPort.description: The local port number for this peer's TCP connection.

alaBgpPeerTcpWindowSize.name: alaBgpPeerTcpWindowSize
alaBgpPeerTcpWindowSize.description: The size of the socket buffers, in bytes, used for this TCP connection.

alaBgpPeerActivateIpv6.name: alaBgpPeerActivateIpv6
alaBgpPeerActivateIpv6.description: If enabled, the Multiprotocol IPv6 Unicast capability is advertised to this peer. If disabled, the capability is not advertised in the OPEN message.

alaBgpPeerBfdStatus.name: alaBgpPeerBfdStatus
alaBgpPeerBfdStatus.description: Enables/Disables BFd for a particular Peer.

alaBgpPeerPrefix6ListOut.name: alaBgpPeerPrefix6ListOut
alaBgpPeerPrefix6ListOut.description: The name of the prefix6-list to be applied to the updates sent to this peer. This is same as alaBgpPrefix6MatchListId.

alaBgpPeerPrefix6ListIn.name: alaBgpPeerPrefix6ListIn
alaBgpPeerPrefix6ListIn.description: The name of the prefix6-list to be applied to the updates received from this peer. This is same as alaBgpPrefix6MatchListId.

alaBgpAggrSummarize.name: alaBgpAggrSummarize
alaBgpAggrSummarize.description: If enabled only aggregate is advertised. Otherwise more specific routes are also advertised.

alaBgpAggrState.name: alaBgpAggrState
alaBgpAggrState.description: if active the aggregate is actively being advertised.

alaBgpAggrMetric.name: alaBgpAggrMetric
alaBgpAggrMetric.description: This specifies the MED to be used when advertising this aggregate to external peers. A value of 0 indicates not to send MED.

alaBgpAggrLocalPref.name: alaBgpAggrLocalPref
alaBgpAggrLocalPref.description: This specifies the override default LOCAL PREF to be used when advertising this aggregate to internal peers. A value of 0 indicates not to override the default.

alaBgpAggrCommunity.name: alaBgpAggrCommunity
alaBgpAggrCommunity.description: The value to set the COMMUNITY attribute when advertising this aggregate.

alaBgpNetworkState.name: alaBgpNetworkState
alaBgpNetworkState.description: Indicates whether the network is being actively advertised or not.

alaBgpNetworkMetric.name: alaBgpNetworkMetric
alaBgpNetworkMetric.description: This specifies the MED to be used when advertising this network to external peers. A value of 0 indicates not to send MED.

alaBgpNetworkLocalPref.name: alaBgpNetworkLocalPref
alaBgpNetworkLocalPref.description: This specifies the override default LOCAL PREF to be used when advertising this network to internal peers. A value of 0 indicates not to override the default.

alaBgpNetworkCommunity.name: alaBgpNetworkCommunity
alaBgpNetworkCommunity.description: The value to set the COMMUNITY attribute when advertising this network.

alaBgpRouteState.name: alaBgpRouteState
alaBgpRouteState.description: Indicates whether the route is being actively advertised or not.

alaBgpRoutePaths.name: alaBgpRoutePaths
alaBgpRoutePaths.description: Number of total paths available to this destination.

alaBgpRouteFeasiblePaths.name: alaBgpRouteFeasiblePaths
alaBgpRouteFeasiblePaths.description: Number of Feasible paths available to this destination.

alaBgpRouteNextHop.name: alaBgpRouteNextHop
alaBgpRouteNextHop.description: The BGP Nexthop to reach this destination.

alaBgpRouteIgpNextHop.name: alaBgpRouteIgpNextHop
alaBgpRouteIgpNextHop.description: The IGP Nexthop to reach this destination.

alaBgpRouteIsHidden.name: alaBgpRouteIsHidden
alaBgpRouteIsHidden.description: Indicates whether the route is hidden by an aggregate.

alaBgpRouteIsAggregate.name: alaBgpRouteIsAggregate
alaBgpRouteIsAggregate.description: Indicates whether the route is an aggregate.

alaBgpRouteIsAggregateContributor.name: alaBgpRouteIsAggregateContributor
alaBgpRouteIsAggregateContributor.description: Indicates whether the route is a contributor to an aggregate.

alaBgpRouteAdvNeighbors.name: alaBgpRouteAdvNeighbors
alaBgpRouteAdvNeighbors.description: List of (addresses of) neighbours to whom this route has been advertised is encoded here.

alaBgpRouteIsAggregateList.name: alaBgpRouteIsAggregateList
alaBgpRouteIsAggregateList.description: Indicates whether the route is on an aggregate list.

alaBgpRouteIsAggregateWait.name: alaBgpRouteIsAggregateWait
alaBgpRouteIsAggregateWait.description: Indicates whether the route is an aggregate waiting for a contributor.

alaBgpRouteIsOnEbgpChgList.name: alaBgpRouteIsOnEbgpChgList
alaBgpRouteIsOnEbgpChgList.description: Indicates whether the route is placed on list of EBGP routes.

alaBgpRouteIsOnIbgpClientChgList.name: alaBgpRouteIsOnIbgpClientChgList
alaBgpRouteIsOnIbgpClientChgList.description: Indicates whether the route is placed on list of IBGP reflector-client routes.

alaBgpRouteIsOnIbgpChgList.name: alaBgpRouteIsOnIbgpChgList
alaBgpRouteIsOnIbgpChgList.description: Indicates whether the route is placed on list of IBGP non-reflector-client routes.

alaBgpRouteIsOnLocalChgList.name: alaBgpRouteIsOnLocalChgList
alaBgpRouteIsOnLocalChgList.description: Indicates whether the route is placed on list of local routes.

alaBgpRouteIsOnDeleteList.name: alaBgpRouteIsOnDeleteList
alaBgpRouteIsOnDeleteList.description: Indicates whether the route is placed on delete list.

alaBgpRouteIsDampened.name: alaBgpRouteIsDampened
alaBgpRouteIsDampened.description: Indicates whether the route is being route flap dampened.

alaBgpPathPeerAddr.name: alaBgpPathPeerAddr
alaBgpPathPeerAddr.description: The IP address or the BGP Identifier of the peer who sent this path. For locally sourced routes, the value is 0.0.0.0. For peers with an IPv4 address, the value will be the peer's IPv4 address, and the value of alaBgpPathPeerInetType will be ipv4. For peers with an IPv6 address, the value will be the peer's BGP Identifier, and the value of alaBgpPathPeerInetType will be ipv6.

alaBgpPathSrcProto.name: alaBgpPathSrcProto
alaBgpPathSrcProto.description: The protocol from which the path was learnt.

alaBgpPathWeight.name: alaBgpPathWeight
alaBgpPathWeight.description: The weight assigned to this path.

alaBgpPathPref.name: alaBgpPathPref
alaBgpPathPref.description: The degree of preference assigned to this path.

alaBgpPathState.name: alaBgpPathState
alaBgpPathState.description: Indicates the state of the path. When path state is none it indicates that there are no paths to this prefix/len and the route is being purged from the system. Stale indicates that the peer that advertised this route's nexthop is in the process of graceful restart.

alaBgpPathOrigin.name: alaBgpPathOrigin
alaBgpPathOrigin.description: The ORIGIN attribute of the path.

alaBgpPathNextHop.name: alaBgpPathNextHop
alaBgpPathNextHop.description: The NEXTHOP attribute of the path.

alaBgpPathAs.name: alaBgpPathAs
alaBgpPathAs.description: The sequence of AS path segments. Each AS path segment is represented by a triple <TYPE, LENGTH, VALUE>. The TYPE is a 1-octet field which has two possible values: (1) AS_SET : unordered set of ASs a route in the UPDATE message has traversed. (2) AS_SEQUENCE : ordered set of ASs a route in the UPDATE message has traversed. The LENGTH is a 1-octet field containing the number of ASs in the value field. The VALUE field contains one or more AS numbers, each AS is represented in the octet string as a pair of octets according to the following algorithm: first-byte-of-pair = ASNumber / 256; second-byte-of-pair = ASNumber & 255;.

alaBgpPathLocalPref.name: alaBgpPathLocalPref
alaBgpPathLocalPref.description: The LOCAL_PREF attribute of the path. A value of -1 indicates the absence of this attribute.

alaBgpPathMed.name: alaBgpPathMed
alaBgpPathMed.description: The Multi Exit Disc. attribute of the path. A value of 4294967295 indicates the absence of this attribute.

alaBgpPathAtomic.name: alaBgpPathAtomic
alaBgpPathAtomic.description: Indicates whether this path is generated without selecting a less specific route.

alaBgpPathAggregatorAs.name: alaBgpPathAggregatorAs
alaBgpPathAggregatorAs.description: The AS number of the last BGP4 speaker that performed route aggregation. A value of 0 indicates the absence of this attribute.

alaBgpPathAggregatorAddr.name: alaBgpPathAggregatorAddr
alaBgpPathAggregatorAddr.description: The IP address of the last BGP4 speaker that performed route aggregation. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates the absence of this attribute.

alaBgpPathCommunity.name: alaBgpPathCommunity
alaBgpPathCommunity.description: The community attribute of the path. The communities are represented as series of 4 octet values.

alaBgpPathUnknownAttr.name: alaBgpPathUnknownAttr
alaBgpPathUnknownAttr.description: One or more path attributes not understood by this BGP4 speaker. Size of zero (0) indicates the absence of such attribute(s). Octets beyond the maximum size, if any, are not recorded by this object.

alaBgpPathOriginatorId.name: alaBgpPathOriginatorId
alaBgpPathOriginatorId.description: The Router Id of the BGP4 speaker that performed route reflection, if this is a reflected route in the local AS. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates the absence of this attribute. Refer RFC 2796 (BGP Route Reflection), Section 7

alaBgpPathClusterList.name: alaBgpPathClusterList
alaBgpPathClusterList.description: Sequence of Cluster Id values representing the reflection path that the route has passed, if this is a reflected route in the local AS. Size of zero (0) indicates the absence of this attribute. Refer RFC 2796 (BGP Route Reflection), Section 7

alaBgpPathPeerInetType.name: alaBgpPathPeerInetType
alaBgpPathPeerInetType.description: Indicates whether the peer who sent this path has an IPv4 address or an IPv6 address. If set to ipv4, the peer has an IPv4 address, and the value of alaBgpPathPeerAddr is the peer's IPv4 address. If set to ipv6, the peer has an IPv6 address, and the value of alaBgpPathPeerAddr is the peer's BGP Identifier. For locally sourced routes, the value is set to unknown.

alaBgpPathPeerName.name: alaBgpPathPeerName
alaBgpPathPeerName.description: The symbolic name of the peer that sent this path. For paths corresponding to local or redistributed routes on this router, the value is set to 'none'.

alaBgpDampFigureOfMerit.name: alaBgpDampFigureOfMerit
alaBgpDampFigureOfMerit.description: The figure of merit value. This is a floating point value with 2 digit precision. For example, a value of 3.5 is encoded as 350, a value of 0.9 is encoded as 90, a value of 9.45 is encoded as 945.

alaBgpDampFlaps.name: alaBgpDampFlaps
alaBgpDampFlaps.description: The number of times this route has flapped.

alaBgpDampDuration.name: alaBgpDampDuration
alaBgpDampDuration.description: Time in seconds since the flap was noticed.

alaBgpDampLastUpdateTime.name: alaBgpDampLastUpdateTime
alaBgpDampLastUpdateTime.description: Time in seconds since this damp entry (figure of merit) was last updated.

alaBgpDampReuseTime.name: alaBgpDampReuseTime
alaBgpDampReuseTime.description: Time in seconds until this route will be reused.

alaBgpDampClear.name: alaBgpDampClear
alaBgpDampClear.description: A value of clear will clear this damp history information.

alaBgpRouteMapAsPathMatchListId.name: alaBgpRouteMapAsPathMatchListId
alaBgpRouteMapAsPathMatchListId.description: This is same as alaBgpAspathMatchListId. It identifies the matching criteria list of Autonomous system paths. Empty quotes indicate no autonomous system paths matching criteria is to be applied.

alaBgpRouteMapPrefixMatchListId.name: alaBgpRouteMapPrefixMatchListId
alaBgpRouteMapPrefixMatchListId.description: This is same as alaBgpPrefixMatchListId. It identifies the matching criteria list of prefixes. Empty quotes indicate no prefix matching criteria is to be applied.

alaBgpRouteMapCommunityMatchListId.name: alaBgpRouteMapCommunityMatchListId
alaBgpRouteMapCommunityMatchListId.description: This is same as alaBgpCommunityMatchListId. It identifies the matching criteria list of communities. Empty quotes indicate no community matching criteria is to be applied.

alaBgpRouteMapOrigin.name: alaBgpRouteMapOrigin
alaBgpRouteMapOrigin.description: The value to set the origin of the routes matched by this RouteMap instance. A value of none means no origin is to be set.

alaBgpRouteMapLocalPref.name: alaBgpRouteMapLocalPref
alaBgpRouteMapLocalPref.description: The value to set the LOCAL PREF attribute of the routes matched by this RouteMap instance. This value is added to/is subtracted from/replaces the LOCAL PREF attribute in conjunction with the associated value of alaBgpRouteMapLocalPrefMode.

alaBgpRouteMapLocalPrefMode.name: alaBgpRouteMapLocalPrefMode
alaBgpRouteMapLocalPrefMode.description: This variable specifies how alaBgpRouteMapLocalPref is to be operated on an existing LPREF attribute of a route on which this RouteMap instance is applied to.

alaBgpRouteMapMed.name: alaBgpRouteMapMed
alaBgpRouteMapMed.description: The value to set the MULTI EXIT DISC attribute of the routes matched by this RouteMap instance. This value is added to/is subtracted from/replaces the MULTI EXIT DISC attribute in conjunction with the associated value of alaBgpRouteMapMedMode.

alaBgpRouteMapMedMode.name: alaBgpRouteMapMedMode
alaBgpRouteMapMedMode.description: This variable specifies how alaBgpRouteMapMed is to be operated on an existing MULTI EXIT DISC attribute of a route on which this RouteMap instance is applied to.

alaBgpRouteMapAsPrepend.name: alaBgpRouteMapAsPrepend
alaBgpRouteMapAsPrepend.description: The value to prepend to the AS_PATH attribute of the routes matched by this RouteMap instance. Empty quotes indicates no AS_PATH prepending is to be done.

alaBgpRouteMapSetCommunityMode.name: alaBgpRouteMapSetCommunityMode
alaBgpRouteMapSetCommunityMode.description: Determines whether alaBgpRouteMapCommunity will be adding to or replacing the COMMUNITY attribute of the routes matched by this RouteMap instance.

alaBgpRouteMapCommunity.name: alaBgpRouteMapCommunity
alaBgpRouteMapCommunity.description: The value to set the COMMUNITY attribute of the routes matched by this RouteMap instance.

alaBgpRouteMapWeight.name: alaBgpRouteMapWeight
alaBgpRouteMapWeight.description: This sets the weight for the incoming route. This parameter has no effect on outbound policy.

alaBgpRouteMapAction.name: alaBgpRouteMapAction
alaBgpRouteMapAction.description: This determines whether to allow a matching route to pass through.

alaBgpAspathMatchListTable.name: alaBgpAspathMatchListTable
alaBgpAspathMatchListTable.description: BGP Policy Aspath criteria matching table.

alaBgpAspathMatchListId.name: alaBgpAspathMatchListId
alaBgpAspathMatchListId.description: Identifier of this list of autonomous system path matching criteria.

alaBgpAspathMatchListRegExp.name: alaBgpAspathMatchListRegExp
alaBgpAspathMatchListRegExp.description: The regular expression identifying the autnomous system paths to be matched by this instance.

alaBgpAspathMatchListPriority.name: alaBgpAspathMatchListPriority
alaBgpAspathMatchListPriority.description: This determines the order in which the matching regular expressions are applied in the list identified by alaBgpAspathMatchListId.

alaBgpAspathMatchListAction.name: alaBgpAspathMatchListAction
alaBgpAspathMatchListAction.description: This determines whether to accept or reject a matching route.

alaBgpAspathMatchListSubIndex.name: alaBgpAspathMatchListSubIndex
alaBgpAspathMatchListSubIndex.description: The primary index of this list.

alaBgpPrefixMatchListTable.name: alaBgpPrefixMatchListTable
alaBgpPrefixMatchListTable.description: BGP Policy prefix matching criteria table.

alaBgpPrefixMatchListId.name: alaBgpPrefixMatchListId
alaBgpPrefixMatchListId.description: Identifier of this list of autonomous system path matching criteria.

alaBgpPrefixMatchListGE.name: alaBgpPrefixMatchListGE
alaBgpPrefixMatchListGE.description: Specifies the minimum length of the mask to be matched. A value of 0 means this criteria is absent. The value of alaBgpPrefixMatchListGE must be > length of (alaBgpPrefixMatchListMask) and < alaBgpPrefixMatchListLE.

alaBgpPrefixMatchListLE.name: alaBgpPrefixMatchListLE
alaBgpPrefixMatchListLE.description: Specifies the maximum length (inclusive) of the mask to be matched. A value of 0 means this criteria is absent. The value of alaBgpPrefixMatchListLE must be >= alaBgpPrefixMatchListGE and <= 32.

alaBgpPrefixMatchListAction.name: alaBgpPrefixMatchListAction
alaBgpPrefixMatchListAction.description: This determines whether to accept or reject a matching route.

alaBgpCommunityMatchListTable.name: alaBgpCommunityMatchListTable
alaBgpCommunityMatchListTable.description: BGP Policy Community criteria matching table.

alaBgpCommunityMatchListId.name: alaBgpCommunityMatchListId
alaBgpCommunityMatchListId.description: Identifier of this list of communities matching criteria.

alaBgpCommunityMatchListString.name: alaBgpCommunityMatchListString
alaBgpCommunityMatchListString.description: The string identifying the communities to be matched by this instance.

alaBgpCommunityMatchListPriority.name: alaBgpCommunityMatchListPriority
alaBgpCommunityMatchListPriority.description: This determines the order in which the matching regular expressions are applied in the list identified by alaBgpCommunityMatchListId.

alaBgpCommunityMatchListAction.name: alaBgpCommunityMatchListAction
alaBgpCommunityMatchListAction.description: This determines whether to accept or reject a matching route.

alaBgpCommunityMatchListSubIndex.name: alaBgpCommunityMatchListSubIndex
alaBgpCommunityMatchListSubIndex.description: The primary index of this list.

alaBgpAspathPriMatchListTable.name: alaBgpAspathPriMatchListTable
alaBgpAspathPriMatchListTable.description: Priority sorted view of BGP Policy Aspath matching table.

alaBgpAspathPriMatchListId.name: alaBgpAspathPriMatchListId
alaBgpAspathPriMatchListId.description: Identifier of this list of autonomous system path matching criteria.

alaBgpAspathPriMatchListPriority.name: alaBgpAspathPriMatchListPriority
alaBgpAspathPriMatchListPriority.description: This determines the order in which the matching regular expressions are applied in the list identified by alaBgpAspathPriMatchListId.

alaBgpAspathPriMatchListIntIdx.name: alaBgpAspathPriMatchListIntIdx
alaBgpAspathPriMatchListIntIdx.description: This is the order in which the matching regular expressions are created in the list identified by alaBgpAspathPriMatchListId.

alaBgpAspathPriMatchListRegExp.name: alaBgpAspathPriMatchListRegExp
alaBgpAspathPriMatchListRegExp.description: The regular expression identifying the autnomous system paths to be matched by this instance

alaBgpAspathPriMatchListAction.name: alaBgpAspathPriMatchListAction
alaBgpAspathPriMatchListAction.description: This determines whether to accept or reject a matching route.

alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListTable.name: alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListTable
alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListTable.description: Priority sorted view of BGP Policy Community matching table.

alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListId.name: alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListId
alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListId.description: Identifier of this list of communities matching criteria.

alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListPriority.name: alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListPriority
alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListPriority.description: This determines the order in which the matching regular expressions are applied in the list identified by alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListId.

alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListIntIdx.name: alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListIntIdx
alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListIntIdx.description: This determines the order in which the matching regular expressions are created in the list identified by alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListId.

alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListString.name: alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListString
alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListString.description: The string identifying the communities to be matched by this instance.

alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListAction.name: alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListAction
alaBgpCommunityPriMatchListAction.description: This determines whether to accept or reject a matching route.

alaBgpPrefix6MatchListTable.name: alaBgpPrefix6MatchListTable
alaBgpPrefix6MatchListTable.description: BGP Policy prefix6 matching criteria table.

alaBgpPrefix6MatchListId.name: alaBgpPrefix6MatchListId
alaBgpPrefix6MatchListId.description: Identifier of this list of autonomous system path matching criteria.

alaBgpPrefix6MatchListAddr.name: alaBgpPrefix6MatchListAddr
alaBgpPrefix6MatchListAddr.description: The IPv6 Prefix to be matched. A value of 0 indicates default route prefix.

alaBgpPrefix6MatchListAddrLength.name: alaBgpPrefix6MatchListAddrLength
alaBgpPrefix6MatchListAddrLength.description: The length in bits of the IPv6 prefix being matched. A value of 0 indicates default route prefix.

alaBgpPrefix6MatchListGE.name: alaBgpPrefix6MatchListGE
alaBgpPrefix6MatchListGE.description: Specifies the minimum length of the mask to be matched. A value of 0 means this criteria is absent. The value of alaBgpPrefix6MatchListGE must be > length of (alaBgpPrefix6MatchListAddrLength) and < alaBgpPrefix6MatchListLE.

alaBgpPrefix6MatchListLE.name: alaBgpPrefix6MatchListLE
alaBgpPrefix6MatchListLE.description: Specifies the maximum length (inclusive) of the mask to be matched. A value of 0 means this criteria is absent. The value of alaBgpPrefix6MatchListLE must be >= alaBgpPrefix6MatchListGE and <= 32.

alaBgpPrefix6MatchListAction.name: alaBgpPrefix6MatchListAction
alaBgpPrefix6MatchListAction.description: This determines whether to accept or reject a matching route.

alaBgpRedistRouteTable.name: alaBgpRedistRouteTable
alaBgpRedistRouteTable.description: A configuration table which controls the routes to be redistributed by BGP from other routing protocols. This table has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoTable of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaBgpRedistRouteEntry.name: alaBgpRedistRouteEntry
alaBgpRedistRouteEntry.description: A configuration table which controls the routes to be redistributed by BGP from other routing protocols. This entry has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaBgpRedistRouteProto.name: alaBgpRedistRouteProto
alaBgpRedistRouteProto.description: Protocol from where this route is to be imported from. This object has been deprecated. Use alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaBgpRedistRouteDest.name: alaBgpRedistRouteDest
alaBgpRedistRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. This object has been deprecated. Use alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaBgpRedistRouteMask.name: alaBgpRedistRouteMask
alaBgpRedistRouteMask.description: The network mask for this route. This object has been deprecated. Use alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaBgpRedistRouteMetric.name: alaBgpRedistRouteMetric
alaBgpRedistRouteMetric.description: The med to be sent to external peers. If 0, no med is sent. This object has been deprecated. Use alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaBgpRedistRouteLocalPref.name: alaBgpRedistRouteLocalPref
alaBgpRedistRouteLocalPref.description: The value to override the default local pref sent to internal peers. If 0, no override is applied. This object has been deprecated. Use alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaBgpRedistRouteCommunity.name: alaBgpRedistRouteCommunity
alaBgpRedistRouteCommunity.description: The value to set the COMMUNITY attribute when advertising this network. This object has been deprecated. Use alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaBgpRedistRouteSubnetMatch.name: alaBgpRedistRouteSubnetMatch
alaBgpRedistRouteSubnetMatch.description: Redistribute all the subnet routes if it is enabled. Otherwise, redistribute only matching network route. This object has been deprecated. Use alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaBgpRedistRouteEffect.name: alaBgpRedistRouteEffect
alaBgpRedistRouteEffect.description: Controls the redistribution of routes in this range. This object has been deprecated. Use alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaBgpRedistRouteRowStatus.name: alaBgpRedistRouteRowStatus
alaBgpRedistRouteRowStatus.description: Row status variable. This object has been deprecated. Use alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaBgpDebugTable.name: alaBgpDebugTable
alaBgpDebugTable.description: BGP debugging table - has been deprecated in favour of alaDrcTmBgpDebug Configuration.

alaBgpDebugEntry.name: alaBgpDebugEntry
alaBgpDebugEntry.description: BGP debugging entry - has been deprecated in favour of alaDrcTmBgpDebug Configuration.

alaBgpDebugEvent.name: alaBgpDebugEvent
alaBgpDebugEvent.description: All the Debug Events/types described here stands deprecated in favour of MIB objects defined in alaDrcTmBgpDebug Configuration.

alaBgpDebugStatus.name: alaBgpDebugStatus
alaBgpDebugStatus.description: All the Debug Events/types described here stands deprecated in favour of MIB objects defined in alaDrcTmBgpDebug Configuration.

alaBgpDebugDescription.name: alaBgpDebugDescription
alaBgpDebugDescription.description: All the Debug Events/types described here stands deprecated in favour of MIB objects defined in alaDrcTmBgpDebug Configuration.

alaBgpNetwork6Addr.name: alaBgpNetwork6Addr
alaBgpNetwork6Addr.description: The IPv6 address of the BGP Network.

alaBgpNetwork6MaskLen.name: alaBgpNetwork6MaskLen
alaBgpNetwork6MaskLen.description: The number of bits that are significant in the IPv6 address prefix of the BGP Network.

alaBgpNetwork6State.name: alaBgpNetwork6State
alaBgpNetwork6State.description: Indicates whether the network is being actively advertised or not.

alaBgpNetwork6Metric.name: alaBgpNetwork6Metric
alaBgpNetwork6Metric.description: This specifies the MED to be used when advertising this network to external peers. A value of 0 indicates not to send MED.

alaBgpNetwork6LocalPref.name: alaBgpNetwork6LocalPref
alaBgpNetwork6LocalPref.description: This specifies the override default LOCAL PREF to be used when advertising this network to internal peers. A value of 0 indicates not to override the default.

alaBgpNetwork6Community.name: alaBgpNetwork6Community
alaBgpNetwork6Community.description: The value to set the COMMUNITY attribute when advertising this network.

alaBgpRoute6State.name: alaBgpRoute6State
alaBgpRoute6State.description: Indicates whether the route is being actively advertised or not.

alaBgpRoute6Paths.name: alaBgpRoute6Paths
alaBgpRoute6Paths.description: Number of total paths available to this destination.

alaBgpRoute6FeasiblePaths.name: alaBgpRoute6FeasiblePaths
alaBgpRoute6FeasiblePaths.description: Number of Feasible paths available to this destination.

alaBgpRoute6NextHop.name: alaBgpRoute6NextHop
alaBgpRoute6NextHop.description: The BGP Nexthop to reach this destination.

alaBgpRoute6IgpNextHop.name: alaBgpRoute6IgpNextHop
alaBgpRoute6IgpNextHop.description: The IGP Nexthop to reach this destination.

alaBgpRoute6IsHidden.name: alaBgpRoute6IsHidden
alaBgpRoute6IsHidden.description: Indicates whether the route is hidden by an aggregate.

alaBgpRoute6IsAggregate.name: alaBgpRoute6IsAggregate
alaBgpRoute6IsAggregate.description: Indicates whether the route is an aggregate.

alaBgpRoute6IsAggregateContributor.name: alaBgpRoute6IsAggregateContributor
alaBgpRoute6IsAggregateContributor.description: Indicates whether the route is a contributor to an aggregate.

alaBgpRoute6AdvNeighbors.name: alaBgpRoute6AdvNeighbors
alaBgpRoute6AdvNeighbors.description: List of (addresses of) neighbours to whom this route has been advertised is encoded here.

alaBgpRoute6IsAggregateList.name: alaBgpRoute6IsAggregateList
alaBgpRoute6IsAggregateList.description: Indicates whether the route is on an aggregate list.

alaBgpRoute6IsAggregateWait.name: alaBgpRoute6IsAggregateWait
alaBgpRoute6IsAggregateWait.description: Indicates whether the route is an aggregate waiting for a contributor.

alaBgpRoute6IsOnEbgpChgList.name: alaBgpRoute6IsOnEbgpChgList
alaBgpRoute6IsOnEbgpChgList.description: Indicates whether the route is placed on list of EBGP routes.

alaBgpRoute6IsOnIbgpClientChgList.name: alaBgpRoute6IsOnIbgpClientChgList
alaBgpRoute6IsOnIbgpClientChgList.description: Indicates whether the route is placed on list of IBGP reflector-client routes.

alaBgpRoute6IsOnIbgpChgList.name: alaBgpRoute6IsOnIbgpChgList
alaBgpRoute6IsOnIbgpChgList.description: Indicates whether the route is placed on list of IBGP non-reflector-client routes.

alaBgpRoute6IsOnLocalChgList.name: alaBgpRoute6IsOnLocalChgList
alaBgpRoute6IsOnLocalChgList.description: Indicates whether the route is placed on list of local routes.

alaBgpRoute6IsOnDeleteList.name: alaBgpRoute6IsOnDeleteList
alaBgpRoute6IsOnDeleteList.description: Indicates whether the route is placed on delete list.

alaBgpRoute6IsDampened.name: alaBgpRoute6IsDampened
alaBgpRoute6IsDampened.description: Indicates whether the route is being route flap dampened.

alaBgpPath6PeerBgpId.name: alaBgpPath6PeerBgpId
alaBgpPath6PeerBgpId.description: The BGP Identifier of the peer who sent this path. For locally sourced routes, the value is 0.0.0.0.

alaBgpPath6SrcProto.name: alaBgpPath6SrcProto
alaBgpPath6SrcProto.description: The protocol from which the path was learnt.

alaBgpPath6Weight.name: alaBgpPath6Weight
alaBgpPath6Weight.description: The weight assigned to this path.

alaBgpPath6Pref.name: alaBgpPath6Pref
alaBgpPath6Pref.description: The degree of preference assigned to this path.

alaBgpPath6State.name: alaBgpPath6State
alaBgpPath6State.description: Indicates the state of the path. When path state is none it indicates that there are no paths to this prefix/len and the route is being purged from the system. Stale indicates that the peer that advertised this route's nexthop is in the process of graceful restart.

alaBgpPath6Origin.name: alaBgpPath6Origin
alaBgpPath6Origin.description: The ORIGIN attribute of the path.

alaBgpPath6NextHop.name: alaBgpPath6NextHop
alaBgpPath6NextHop.description: The NEXTHOP attribute of the path.

alaBgpPath6As.name: alaBgpPath6As
alaBgpPath6As.description: The sequence of AS path segments. Each AS path segment is represented by a triple <TYPE, LENGTH, VALUE>. The TYPE is a 1-octet field which has two possible values: (1) AS_SET : unordered set of ASs a route in the UPDATE message has traversed. (2) AS_SEQUENCE : ordered set of ASs a route in the UPDATE message has traversed. The LENGTH is a 1-octet field containing the number of ASs in the value field. The VALUE field contains one or more AS numbers, each AS is represented in the octet string as a pair of octets according to the following algorithm: first-byte-of-pair = ASNumber / 256; second-byte-of-pair = ASNumber & 255;

alaBgpPath6LocalPref.name: alaBgpPath6LocalPref
alaBgpPath6LocalPref.description: The LOCAL_PREF attribute of the path. A value of -1 indicates the absence of this attribute.

alaBgpPath6Med.name: alaBgpPath6Med
alaBgpPath6Med.description: The Multi Exit Disc. attribute of the path. A value of 4294967295 indicates the absence of this attribute.

alaBgpPath6Atomic.name: alaBgpPath6Atomic
alaBgpPath6Atomic.description: Indicates whether this path is generated without selecting a less specific route.

alaBgpPath6AggregatorAs.name: alaBgpPath6AggregatorAs
alaBgpPath6AggregatorAs.description: The AS number of the last BGP4 speaker that performed route aggregation. A value of 0 indicates the absence of this attribute.

alaBgpPath6AggregatorAddr.name: alaBgpPath6AggregatorAddr
alaBgpPath6AggregatorAddr.description: The IP address of the last BGP4 speaker that performed route aggregation. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates the absence of this attribute.

alaBgpPath6Community.name: alaBgpPath6Community
alaBgpPath6Community.description: The community attribute of the path. The communities are represented as series of 4 octet values.

alaBgpPath6UnknownAttr.name: alaBgpPath6UnknownAttr
alaBgpPath6UnknownAttr.description: One or more path attributes not understood by this BGP4 speaker. Size of zero (0) indicates the absence of such attribute(s). Octets beyond the maximum size, if any, are not recorded by this object.

alaBgpPath6OriginatorId.name: alaBgpPath6OriginatorId
alaBgpPath6OriginatorId.description: The Router Id of the BGP4 speaker that performed route reflection, if this is a reflected route in the local AS. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates the absence of this attribute. Refer RFC 2796 (BGP Route Reflection), Section 7

alaBgpPath6ClusterList.name: alaBgpPath6ClusterList
alaBgpPath6ClusterList.description: Sequence of Cluster Id values representing the reflection path that the route has passed, if this is a reflected route in the local AS. Size of zero (0) indicates the absence of this attribute. Refer RFC 2796 (BGP Route Reflection), Section 7

alaBgpPath6PeerName.name: alaBgpPath6PeerName
alaBgpPath6PeerName.description: The symbolic name of the peer that sent this path. For paths corresponding to local or redistributed routes on this router, the value is set to 'none'.

alaBgpPeer6Passive.name: alaBgpPeer6Passive
alaBgpPeer6Passive.description: Enable/Disable the peer passive status. If enabled the peer will not initiate a transport connection.

alaBgpPeer6Name.name: alaBgpPeer6Name
alaBgpPeer6Name.description: A symbolic name for the neighbour.

alaBgpPeer6MultiHop.name: alaBgpPeer6MultiHop
alaBgpPeer6MultiHop.description: If enabled the external peer is allowed to be multiple hops away.

alaBgpPeer6MaxPrefix.name: alaBgpPeer6MaxPrefix
alaBgpPeer6MaxPrefix.description: The maximum prefixes to be accepted from this peer. If this maximum is reached, the peer will be sent a NOTIFY message with a CEASE ecode.

alaBgpPeer6MaxPrefixWarnOnly.name: alaBgpPeer6MaxPrefixWarnOnly
alaBgpPeer6MaxPrefixWarnOnly.description: If enabled, the operator will be warned when the peer reaches 80% of the configured maximum prefixes. To see this message, BGP debug for type 'warnings' must be activated and debug level set to 20.

alaBgpPeer6NextHopSelf.name: alaBgpPeer6NextHopSelf
alaBgpPeer6NextHopSelf.description: If enabled, nexthop processing in the updates sent to this peer is disabled and is set to the IPv6 address of the interface attached to this peer.

alaBgpPeer6SoftReconfig.name: alaBgpPeer6SoftReconfig
alaBgpPeer6SoftReconfig.description: Enable/Disable dynamic policy configurability on the connection to this peer.

alaBgpPeer6InSoftReset.name: alaBgpPeer6InSoftReset
alaBgpPeer6InSoftReset.description: Route refresh capability is Enabled/Disabled on the connection to this peer.

alaBgpPeer6Ipv4Unicast.name: alaBgpPeer6Ipv4Unicast
alaBgpPeer6Ipv4Unicast.description: Multiprotocol capability IPv4 Unicast is Enabled/Disabled on the connection to this peer .

alaBgpPeer6Ipv4Multicast.name: alaBgpPeer6Ipv4Multicast
alaBgpPeer6Ipv4Multicast.description: Multiprotocol capability IPv4 Multicast is Enabled/Disabled on the connection to this peer .

alaBgpPeer6RcvdRtRefreshMsgs.name: alaBgpPeer6RcvdRtRefreshMsgs
alaBgpPeer6RcvdRtRefreshMsgs.description: The number of route refresh messages received from this peer.

alaBgpPeer6SentRtRefreshMsgs.name: alaBgpPeer6SentRtRefreshMsgs
alaBgpPeer6SentRtRefreshMsgs.description: The number of route refresh messages sent to this peer.

alaBgpPeer6RouteMapOut.name: alaBgpPeer6RouteMapOut
alaBgpPeer6RouteMapOut.description: The name of the policy map to be applied to the updates sent to this peer. This is same as alaBgpPolicyRouteMapName.

alaBgpPeer6RouteMapIn.name: alaBgpPeer6RouteMapIn
alaBgpPeer6RouteMapIn.description: The name of the policy map to be applied to the updates received from this peer. This is same as alaBgpPolicyRouteMapName.

alaBgpPeer6LocalAddr.name: alaBgpPeer6LocalAddr
alaBgpPeer6LocalAddr.description: Local IPv6 address of this connection.

alaBgpPeer6LastDownReason.name: alaBgpPeer6LastDownReason
alaBgpPeer6LastDownReason.description: The general reason for termination of last established session with the peer since the protocol was operationally up.

alaBgpPeer6LastDownTime.name: alaBgpPeer6LastDownTime
alaBgpPeer6LastDownTime.description: The time elapsed since the BGP session with the peer was terminated.

alaBgpPeer6LastReadTime.name: alaBgpPeer6LastReadTime
alaBgpPeer6LastReadTime.description: The time elapsed since we last read data from the peer.

alaBgpPeer6RcvdNotifyMsgs.name: alaBgpPeer6RcvdNotifyMsgs
alaBgpPeer6RcvdNotifyMsgs.description: The Number of notification messages received from this peer.

alaBgpPeer6SentNotifyMsgs.name: alaBgpPeer6SentNotifyMsgs
alaBgpPeer6SentNotifyMsgs.description: The Number of notification messages sent to this peer.

alaBgpPeer6RcvdPrefixes.name: alaBgpPeer6RcvdPrefixes
alaBgpPeer6RcvdPrefixes.description: The Number of prefixes received from this peer.

alaBgpPeer6DownTransitions.name: alaBgpPeer6DownTransitions
alaBgpPeer6DownTransitions.description: The Number of times this peer session transitioned to IDLE state.

alaBgpPeer6Type.name: alaBgpPeer6Type
alaBgpPeer6Type.description: This indicates whether the peer belongs to the local autonomous system(internal) or another autonomous system.

alaBgpPeer6HoldTime.name: alaBgpPeer6HoldTime
alaBgpPeer6HoldTime.description: Time interval in seconds for the Hold Timer established with the peer. The value of this object is calculated by this BGP speaker by using the smaller of the value in alaBgpPeer6HoldTimeConfigured and the Hold Time received in the OPEN message. This value must be at lease three seconds if it is not zero (0) in which case the session has not been established with the peer, or, the value of alaBgpPeer6HoldTimeConfigured is zero (0).

alaBgpPeer6KeepAlive.name: alaBgpPeer6KeepAlive
alaBgpPeer6KeepAlive.description: Time interval in seconds for the KeepAlive timer established with the peer. The value of this object is calculated by this BGP speaker such that, when compared with alaBgpPeer6HoldTime, it has the same proportion as what alaBgpPeer6KeepAliveConfigured has when compared with alaBgpPeer6HoldTimeConfigured. If the value of this object is zero (0), it indicates that the session has not been established with the peer, or, the value of alaBgpPeer6KeepAliveConfigured is zero (0).

alaBgpPeer6ConnRetryInterval.name: alaBgpPeer6ConnRetryInterval
alaBgpPeer6ConnRetryInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the ConnectRetry timer. The suggested value for this timer is 120 seconds.

alaBgpPeer6HoldTimeConfigured.name: alaBgpPeer6HoldTimeConfigured
alaBgpPeer6HoldTimeConfigured.description: Time interval in seconds for the Hold Time configured for this BGP speaker with this peer. This value is placed in an OPEN message sent to this peer by this BGP speaker, and is compared with the Hold Time field in an OPEN message received from the peer when determining the Hold Time (alaBgpPeer6HoldTime) with the peer. This value must not be less than three seconds if it is not zero (0) in which case the Hold Time is NOT to be negotiated with the peer. The suggested value for this timer is 90 seconds.

alaBgpPeer6KeepAliveConfigured.name: alaBgpPeer6KeepAliveConfigured
alaBgpPeer6KeepAliveConfigured.description: Time interval in seconds for the KeepAlive timer configured for this BGP speaker with this peer. The value of this object will only determine the KEEPALIVE messages' frequency relative to the value specified in alaBgpPeer6HoldTimeConfigured; the actual time interval for the KEEPALIVE messages is indicated by alaBgpPeer6KeepAlive. A reasonable maximum value for this timer would be configured to be one third of that of alaBgpPeer6HoldTimeConfigured. If the value of this object is zero (0), no periodical KEEPALIVE messages are sent to the peer after the BGP connection has been established. The suggested value for this timer is 30 seconds.
